{"word":"λάρναξ","slug":"λάρναξ","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>λάρναξ</b></el> <el>(λάρναξ, ακος,) </el><p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>a coffer, box, chest</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>a cinerary urn</i> or <i>coffin</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><i>an ark</i>, in which children were exposed, <b><a href='S:Simonides Lyricus'>Simon.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}